ted that vitol in concert with the abu dhabi investment council had bought the downstream businesses of shell australia excluding aviation for a total of approximately au billion the purchase included shells geelong refinery and its site retail business along with its bulk fuels bitumen chemicals and part of its lubricants businesses in australia the business trades as viva energy australia although the shell brand remains on many of its retail products further in january  vitol in collaboration with eni signed a  billion agreement with the government for the production of oil and gas at cape three points in western region of ghana the contract is expected to help meet ghanas burgeoning energy needs aviationedit vitol aviation is focused on europe north america and africa serving the world’s largest airlines and military customers with  million tonnes of jet fuel a year into wing poweredit in  vitol invested in its first power plant vpi immingham in the uk the combined heat and power plant chp is one of the largest of its kind in europe capable of generating  mw and up to  tonnes of steam per hour which is used by nearby refineries the gasfired plant provides approximately  of uk peak electricity demand figuresedit in  vitol traded oil  million tonnes of crude oil and product sales natural gas over  billion cubic meters of physical gas globally lpg  million tonnes naphtha  million tonnes gasoline  million barrels of physical gasoline traded per day coal over  million tonnes power  twh of power sales contracted carbon  mm tonnes of contracted carbon volume methanol  million tonnes chemicals  million tonnes benzene and paraxylene controversiesedit a  article in the observer stated that in  vitol had secretly paid us million to serbian war criminal arkan to settle a deal with a serbian oil company orion vitol has denied all charges arguing that no government agency has ever prosecuted the company in this respect in  vitol pleaded guilty to grand larceny in a new york court for paying surcharges to iraqs national oil company during saddams regime and circumventing the un oilforfood program vitol subsequently paid  million in restitution for its actions according to an article in the financial times vitol was the company to organise the first controversial sale of libyan rebel oil to tesoro corporation in early april  according to the financial times the company was approached by the qatari national oil company to sell a cargo of crude oil supplied by the libyans in exchange for technological supplies and fuel for the national transitional council of libya in september  an article in reuters alleged that the company had bought and sold iranian fuel oil bypassing an eu embargo against tehran vitol bought  million barrels using a shiptoship transfer off the coast of malaysia from a national iranian tanker company vessel and sold it to chinese traders the article stated that as vitol is based in switzerland which did not implement western sanctions vitol had skirted the charges in  the telegraph alleged that the company had been using for over a decade an employee benefit trust avoiding paying income tax for its uk staff see alsoedit energy law bob finch referencesedit  a b c d meet the mysterious trading firms who control the price of commodities businessnews  retrieved    a b c schneyer joshua  commodity traders the trillion dollar club reuters retrieved    vitol holding bv private company information bloomberg businessweek retrieved  january    a b okeefe brian the unseen hand that moves the worlds oil fortune retrieved  february    rosco announces cash offer for arawak oil voice  retrieved    blas javier  march  vitol said to post highest profit since  as oil prices swing bloomberg retrieved  october    schneyer joshua corrected commodity traders the trillion dollar club reuters retrieved  october    hume neil  march  oil trader vitol’s profits rebound to bn financial times retrieved  october    subscribe to read financial times  