f vitol remarked “we are delighted to be adding the antwerp facilities to our existing asset base this processing and storage facility is well placed in the major refining and trading hub in north west europe it will add significant storage capacity to our existing terminal business and obvious synergies with our global operations” founded in  the vitol group operates worldwide and is one of the worlds largest private integrated oil companies with a turnover of  billion in  vitol moves over  million barrels per day of physical crude oil and oil products in addition to antwerp vitol also has a refinery in fujairah and a long term contract to manage the crude oil supply and product offtake for the north atlantic refinery in newfoundland the storage and terminals company vtti has a number of major terminals in amsterdam rotterdam fujairah and argentina as well as a  shareholding in the ventspils terminal in latvia current storage capacity worldwide is over  million cubic metres petroplus holdings ag is the largest independent refiner and wholesaler of petroleum products in europe petroplus focuses on refining and currently owns and operates seven refineries across europe the refineries have a combined throughput capacity of approximately  barrels per day further details on the vitol group can be found at wwwvitolcom and on vtti at wwwvtticom for further information finsbury londonandrew mitchell      cohn and wolfe amsterdamerik graadt van roggen      cohn and wolfe genevavictoria dix     for further details on petroplus on wwwpetroplusholdingscom tom trovato irpetroplusbiz or      location headquarters share share on facebook share on twitter share on google plus media enquiries for all media enquiries please contact lisanne kosters vtti pr  communications        send email next story nd march  first gas delivered to new world class lpg terminal in nigeria vitol today announced that the first shipment of lpg has been safely delivered to the brand new navgas lpg terminal in the port of lagos navgas nigeria current story rd october  vitol enters into a definitive agreement to acquire antwerp refining facilities from petroplus vtti and its wholly owned subsidiary eurotank belgium bv part of the vitol group of companies “vitol” entered today into a share purchase agreement vtti previous story th august  vitol tank terminals international bv enters a joint venture agreement with misc berhad vtti part of the vitol group entered into a joint venture agreement today with misc berhad to incorporate a joint venture company on an equal partnership basis vtti view all news vtti about us customers health safety  environment terminals and projects news media  downloads contact terminals atb malaysia atpc belgium att croatia bnk russia eta the netherlands ett the netherlands ipos us virgin islands navgas nigeria patsa panama seaport canaveral usa vitco argentina vnt latvia vtti ftl uae vtti kenya mombasa vttv cyprus projects rotan pipeline burgan cape terminals south africa vtti careers connected talent investing in you meet our people location  opportunities careers contact terms of use legal disclaimer privacy policy cookie policy   vtti all rights reserved email please complete the following form to contact  indicates a mandatory field there are some errors or omissions in your details below please update your details and try again full name  company email address  message  captcha  send email thank you your message has been sent successfully return to site